Import Data Browser-Gender - Users

DA <-  read_excel("~/Desktop/Job related/Surefoot/Surefoot 2/Surefoot- GA/Analysis - 2/test and control dates/Users+ Browser/browser+gender.xlsx", sheet = 2)

Data wrangling

DA_01 <- DA 
 
  
colnames(DA_01)[colnames(DA_01)=="New Users"] <- "New_Users"  
colnames(DA_01)[colnames(DA_01)=="Date Range"] <- "Date_Range" 
colnames(DA_01)[colnames(DA_01)=="Bounce Rate"] <- "Bounce_Rate"
colnames(DA_01)[colnames(DA_01)=="Pages / Session"] <- "Page_Sesion"
colnames(DA_01)[colnames(DA_01)=="Avg. Session Duration"] <- "Avg_Session_Duration"
colnames(DA_01)[colnames(DA_01)=="Ecommerce Conversion Rate"] <- "E_Conversion_Rate"
 
  

DA_02 <- DA_01 %>% filter(!is.na(Browser))

DA_03 <- DA_02 %>% mutate(test_categ = ifelse(Date_Range == "Oct 18, 2019 - Oct 31, 2019", "test-Oct 18,2019 - Oct 31,2019", "control-Oct 4,2019 - Oct 17,2019"))

DG_m <- DA_03 %>% filter(Date_Range == "Oct 18, 2019 - Oct 31, 2019")

Visualization Gender- Browser Users

DA_20 <- DA_03 %>% select( Browser, Gender, Revenue, test_categ)
 
  
DA_24 <- DA_20 %>% select(Browser, Gender, Revenue, test_categ) %>% group_by(Browser, Gender, test_categ) %>% mutate(TotR = sum(Revenue)) %>% select(Browser, Gender, TotR,  test_categ)
DA_25 <- unique(DA_24) 
 

DA_25$Gender<- as.factor(DA_25$Gender) 
DA_25 %>% filter(TotR > 0) %>% 
ggplot(aes(reorder(x=Browser, TotR), y=TotR, fill=Gender)) + 
  geom_bar(stat="identity", position = "dodge")  + theme(plot.title = element_text(size =10),axis.text.x = element_text(size =7,angle = 65, hjust = 1) ) + ggtitle("Browser by Gender for Users") +xlab("Browser") + ylab("Total Revenue") +  scale_fill_manual(values=c("#F8766D", "#39B600",  "#9590FF", "#FF62BC", "#D89000", "#00C1A3", "#A3A500", "#EA8331", "#00BFCD", "#00B4F0", "#00BFC4" )) + guides(colour = guide_legend(override.aes = list(size=3, alpha = 1))) + scale_shape_manual(values=c(3:9)) + facet_wrap(~test_categ)

Import Data Browser-Device - Users

DA <-  read_excel("~/Desktop/Job related/Surefoot/Surefoot 2/Surefoot- GA/Analysis - 2/test and control dates/Users+ Browser/browser+device.xlsx", sheet = 2)

Data wrangling

DA_01 <- DA 
 names(DA)
##  [1] "Browser"                   "Device Category"          
##  [3] "Date Range"                "Users"                    
##  [5] "New Users"                 "Sessions"                 
##  [7] "Bounce Rate"               "Pages / Session"          
##  [9] "Avg. Session Duration"     "Ecommerce Conversion Rate"
## [11] "Transactions"              "Revenue"
colnames(DA_01)[colnames(DA_01)=="New Users"] <- "New_Users"  
colnames(DA_01)[colnames(DA_01)=="Date Range"] <- "Date_Range" 
colnames(DA_01)[colnames(DA_01)=="Bounce Rate"] <- "Bounce_Rate"
colnames(DA_01)[colnames(DA_01)=="Pages / Session"] <- "Page_Sesion"
colnames(DA_01)[colnames(DA_01)=="Avg. Session Duration"] <- "Avg_Session_Duration"
colnames(DA_01)[colnames(DA_01)=="Ecommerce Conversion Rate"] <- "E_Conversion_Rate"
colnames(DA_01)[colnames(DA_01)=="Device Category"] <- "Device"
 
  

DA_02 <- DA_01 %>% filter(!is.na(Browser))

DA_03 <- DA_02 %>% mutate(test_categ = ifelse(Date_Range == "Oct 18, 2019 - Oct 31, 2019", "test-Oct 18,2019 - Oct 31,2019", "control-Oct 4,2019 - Oct 17,2019"))

DD_m <- DA_03 %>% filter(Date_Range == "Oct 18, 2019 - Oct 31, 2019")

Visualization Device - Browser Users

DA_20 <- DA_03 %>% select( Browser, Device, Revenue, Users, test_categ)
 
  
DA_24 <- DA_20 %>% select(Browser, Device, Users, Revenue, test_categ) %>% group_by(Browser, Device, test_categ, Users) %>% mutate(TotR = sum(Revenue)) %>% select(Browser, Users, Device, TotR,  test_categ)
DA_25 <- unique(DA_24) 
 

DA_25$Device<- as.factor(DA_25$Device) 
DA_25 %>% filter(TotR >0 ) %>% 
ggplot(aes(reorder(x=Browser, TotR), y=TotR, fill=Device)) + 
  geom_bar(stat="identity", position = "dodge")  + theme(plot.title = element_text(size =10),axis.text.x = element_text(size =7,angle = 65, hjust = 1) ) + ggtitle("Browser by Device for Users") +xlab("Browser") + ylab("Total Revenue") +  scale_fill_manual(values=c("#F8766D", "#39B600",  "#9590FF", "#FF62BC", "#D89000", "#00C1A3", "#A3A500", "#EA8331", "#00BFCD", "#00B4F0", "#00BFC4" )) + guides(colour = guide_legend(override.aes = list(size=3, alpha = 1))) + scale_shape_manual(values=c(3:9)) + facet_wrap(~test_categ)
